. Comparisons of industry structure in differing regulatory environments lead to the conclusion that entry controls are not justified by their results.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aLicenseszOntario. 0aTrade regulationzOntario. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political Economy.2bisacsh1 aBossons, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMakuch, S.M., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aMakuch, S.M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPalmer, John, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aPalmer, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aQuance, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aQuance, Peter.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press eBook-Package Archive 1933-1999z978311049094740uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144263226440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442632264423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442632264.jpg  a978-3-11-049094-7  University of Toronto Press eBook-Package Archive 1933-1999c1933d1999  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK